ACT:
 Andhra Pradesh Land Reforms (Ceiling on Agricultural Holdings) Act, 1973, Section 3(f), definition of family unit-Whether the term "minor sons" would include a "separated minor son" long before the coming into force of the Act and whether the lands transferred by such separated minor sons to third parties by separate sale deeds would also form part of a holding for the purposes of Sections 3(f), 3(0), 4, 5(3), 5(4), 7, Explanations I and II to Sections 8 and 10-Whether to answer in the affirmative and holding so would be in violation of Articles 14 and 21 of the Constitution-Whether a new plea not taken before the High Court would be allowed to be taken for the first time in the Supreme Court and a petitioner be given liberty to produce a document in future.
 
